cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with metric learning methods for dimensionality reduction, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The paper also discusses classification and information retrieval applications, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.CL. However, the focus on shallow parametric data embedding and the use of a specific objective function (MCML) suggests that the paper is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of benchmark datasets and comparisons with state-of-the-art approaches further supports this categorization. The paper may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) due to the use of embedding techniques for image data.
